# LLM Text Adventure Engine

SQLite-backed interactive fiction engine for AI agents. The engine owns canonical state; agents (like Hermes) handle narration and propose structured changes.

**The engine remembers. The agent imagines.**

For a plain-language guide to concepts and workflows, see [`adventures.md`](adventures.md). For the full design spec, see [`project_spec.md`](project_spec.md).

---

## Setup

```bash
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

## Quick start

```bash
ta init-db
ta import examples/world_seed.json
ta --world house_by_sea new-session
ta --world house_by_sea play "look"
ta --world house_by_sea play "take brass key"
ta --world house_by_sea play "go north"
ta --world house_by_sea context
```

Default database path: `~/.text_adventure/engine.db` (override with `--db`).

---

## Worlds, sessions, and saves

- **Worlds** — a complete adventure setting (rooms, items, NPCs, exits). Many worlds can live in one database; select with `--world <id>`.
- **Session** — one active playthrough per world (location, inventory, flags, known rooms, NPC state).
- **Save** — a named snapshot you can load later. Export dumps the committed world layout, not player progress.

---

## CLI commands

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `ta init-db` | Create or upgrade the SQLite database |
| `ta import <seed.json>` | Import a world seed |
| `ta --world <id> export` | Export committed world JSON (`-o` to write a file) |
| `ta --world <id> new-session` | Start a new active session |
| `ta --world <id> session` | Show active session state |
| `ta --world <id> list-saves` | List named saves |
| `ta --world <id> save <name>` | Snapshot current session (`--overwrite` to replace) |
| `ta --world <id> load <name>` | Load a named save as the active session |
| `ta --world <id> play "<input>"` | Apply player input (`--json` for structured result) |
| `ta --world <id> show-room` | Show current room (`--json` optional) |
| `ta --world <id> show-map` | Show known rooms |
| `ta --world <id> context` | Agent context bundle (`--author` for GM view; `--input` for candidates) |
| `ta --world <id> events` | Export event log as JSONL (`-o` optional) |
| `ta --world <id> draft add <file>` | Create draft from JSON |
| `ta --world <id> draft from-narration <file>` | Attach last LLM narration as source text |
| `ta --world <id> draft list` | List drafts (`--all-statuses` optional) |
| `ta --world <id> draft show <id>` | Show a draft |
| `ta --world <id> draft revise <id> <file>` | Replace draft payload |
| `ta --world <id> draft commit <id>` | Validate and commit draft to world |
| `ta --world <id> draft reject <id>` | Reject a draft |
| `ta --world <id> apply-patch <file>` | Apply a patch JSON file |
| `ta --world <id> roll dice <expr>` | Roll dice (e.g. `1d6+2`, `2d10+3`) |
| `ta --world <id> roll coin` | Flip a coin |
| `ta --world <id> roll deck <name>` | Draw from a deck in world metadata |
| `ta --world <id> roll table <name>` | Choose from a weighted table in world metadata |

Standalone entry points: `ta-play`, `ta-save`, `ta-load`, `ta-export`, `ta-import`, `ta-context`, `ta-draft`, `ta-apply-patch`, `ta-roll`, etc.

---

## Playing

The engine matches input against action labels/aliases and built-in verbs:

| Verb | Examples |
|---|---|
| Movement / interaction | Matched against room actions (`go north`, `listen to the house`) |
| `look` | Room description, exits, items |
| `examine` / `x` | Item description (may trigger `on_examine` effects) |
| `take` / `get`, `drop` | Move portable items |
| `inventory` / `i` | List carried items |
| `use X on Y` | Item-on-target puzzle rules (also `with`, `against`) |
| `talk to X` | Free NPC conversation (agent narrates) |
| `ask X about Y` | Topic dialogue with canon facts and effects |

Conditions use the `requires` DSL: `flags.*`, `inventory.*`, with `!` negation.

---

## Agent integration

Use `ta context` (or `build_agent_context()` in Python) for current room, visible exits/items/NPCs, inventory, flags, known rooms, recent events, available actions, and active drafts.

- **Player context** (default) — spoiler-safe; hidden content filtered.
- **Author context** (`--author`) — includes hidden rooms, hidden exits, and full NPC topics/metadata.

Each `play --json` result may include:

| Field | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `parsed_action` / `parsed_action_id` | What the engine understood |
| `requires_agent` | Agent should narrate or interpret further |
| `state_changes` | Mechanical updates applied |
| `blank_exit_triggered` / `proposed_draft` | Blank exit hit; destination not yet committed |
| `candidate_actions` | Partial matches when input could not be resolved |
| `npc_talk` | NPC brief, topic, and canon facts for dialogue |
| `roll_request` | Reserved hook for agent-initiated rolls |

Agents propose world changes as JSON **drafts** or **patches**; the engine validates and commits.

---

## Authoring

### Drafts

Propose content before it becomes canonical. Revise, commit, or reject.

```bash
ta --world house_by_sea play "go west" --json          # blank_exit_triggered
# Agent writes examples/draft_room_from_narration.json
ta --world house_by_sea draft add examples/draft_room_from_narration.json
ta --world house_by_sea draft commit draft_cold_gallery_001
ta --world house_by_sea play "go west"
```

Committing a room draft can update an existing **blank exit** in place (aliases merged).

### Patches

Direct validated mutations: `add_room`, `add_exit`, `update_exit`, `add_item`, `set_flag`, `batch_add_region`, and more.

```bash
ta --world house_by_sea apply-patch examples/commit_patch_example.json
ta --world house_by_sea apply-patch examples/hidden_region_patch.json
```

### Hidden regions

Rooms committed as `hidden` exist in the world but are filtered from player context until discovered.

| Mechanism | Effect |
|---|---|
| `discover_rooms` in effects | Room name appears on map as `[known]` before visiting |
| `reveal_exits` in effects | Hidden exit visible for this save (e.g. `"kitchen:down_to_cellar"`) |
| Movement into hidden room | Marks known + visited; logs `room_discovered` |
| Hidden exit + `requires` | Exit auto-shows when requirements met |

Use `batch_add_region` with `"default_room_status": "hidden"`. Keep **entry** exits hidden; mark **internal** region exits `"status": "committed"`.

### Use X on Y

Puzzle rules on items (tool must be in inventory):

1. Explicit `properties.use_on.<target_id>`
2. Target `properties.accepts_use.<tool_id>`
3. Key pattern: `key_for` + target `locked` / `unlock_flag`

### NPC dialogue

NPC `metadata` supplies a **brief** (voice, role, wants, wont) for agent roleplay — not pre-written lines.

- **Free talk** — engine logs attempt, returns brief; agent performs dialogue.
- **Topics** — `metadata.topics.<name>` with optional `requires`, `facts`, and `effects` (including `set_state` per save).

```bash
ta --world house_by_sea play "talk to cat"
ta --world house_by_sea play "ask cat about pantry"
```

---

## Randomness

Rolls are engine-owned and logged (seed + draw count per session):

```bash
ta --world house_by_sea roll dice "1d6+2" --reason "Luck check"
ta --world house_by_sea roll coin --reason "Which way?"
ta --world house_by_sea roll deck tarot_minor
ta --world house_by_sea roll table weather
```

Decks and tables are defined in `world.metadata.decks` and `world.metadata.tables`.

---

## Persistence

- SQLite with WAL and foreign keys
- Append-only **events** and **transcripts**
- **Random events** logged separately
- World **import/export** as JSON
- One **active session** per world

